  "text": "The I-S transformation is recognized in sedimentary basins worldwide. In the SSK-1D well, the alteration of dioctahedral smectite to I-S conforms to the illitization reaction with an increasing amount of illite layers in response to increasing burial depth. The I-S diagenesis is similar to that of the Gulf Coast [CITATION_1] , although trioctahedral smectite and C-S are also present. In the SSK-1D well, the clay mineralogical changes are probably the result of temperature increase associated with burial, because no evidence of igneous or hydrothermal activity was found in the study area.",
